                <head>314. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On March 12, the National Committee of the Austrian People’s Party, which held a
                    plurality in Parliament, called for national elections on May 10. According to
                    airgram G–316 from Vienna, March 13, <persName corresp="#p_RJ1">Raab</persName>,
                    leader of the People’s Party, had reached the decision in February to move up
                    the date for elections from the fall to the spring of 1959 as a means of
                    exerting pressure on its governing coalition partner, the Austrian Socialist
                    Party, led by <persName corresp="#p_PB1">Pittermann</persName>. (Department of
                    State, Central Files, 763.00/3–1359)</p>
            </div>
